## Risk Rating: High

Data exfiltration directly threatens confidentiality and can carry regulatory/reputational consequences regardless of volume. Rated high pending DLP confirmation — the cost of under-reacting to a false negative here is high enough to justify escalation on suspicious pattern alone.

## Recommendations

- Escalate to DLP/full packet capture review to determine actual data content and volume transferred, if any.
- Block the destination IP/domain pending reputation confirmation.
- Isolate the endpoint if staging behavior (bulk access, archiving) is confirmed in follow-up review.
- Force credential reset for the associated account as a precaution.
- Review DLP policy coverage for the file shares/data types potentially involved — close any gaps that let this go undetected until network-layer alerting caught it.
- Implement egress filtering/allowlisting for sensitive network segments to reduce future exfiltration surface.

## Detection Query Example (KQL)

```kql
DeviceNetworkEvents
| where RemoteIPType == "Public"
| summarize TotalBytes = sum(TotalBytesSent), Connections = count() by DeviceName, RemoteIP, bin(Timestamp, 1h)
| where TotalBytes > 500000000
| order by TotalBytes desc
```

